      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Pathfinder #71: Rasputin Must Die! pg. 64</em></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 1,000 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 20 lbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Damage</strong> 2d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> 100 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P; <strong>Special</strong> automatic</p>\n<p><strong>Misfire</strong> 1-2; <strong>Capacity</strong> 20, 30, or 40</p>\n<p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3>\n<p>This imposing machine gun is light enough to be transported and wielded by a single user. Chambered for the Russian military in 7.62 54mmR, this machine gun uses a top-loading, detachable 20-, 30-, or 40-round magazine.</p>\n<p>Like most machine guns, it is only capable of automatic fire.</p>",
